name: abangan waterfall
address: Br. Gitgit, Bakbakan, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80515, Indonesia
review 1:
most beautiful waterfall, we had the place to ourselves so it fell like a private visit. Aluf took so many pictures of us, he was soo sweet that even gave us a papaya from the tree next to the waterfall.
Definitely worth to come back
review 2: Beautiful place, very big waterfall, probably the highest of all the nearby, the place is not very promoted yet and there are very few tourists, we were met by a local guy and had a personalized tour, was very polite and attentive. We had a great time.
review 3: Most amazing waterfall,we had so much fun, the ppl there are very kind and welcoming, you go throw the rice fields then some stairs and then you are in heaven, price is 20k.
review 4: Such a beautiful waterfall! We were lucky to be the only ones there, got to swim, climbed the waterfall and just relax in nature. The locals at the entrance were super friendly, and there is a little warung right next to the entrance to eat before or after your visit to the waterfall.
review 5: Rather unknown and new, but such a beautiful and hidden place. The owner personally took us down and took some gorgeous photos and videos for us. Man made steps down the jungle through rice terraces towards the river. The trek can be a little difficult for older individuals or people with bad knees (the steps are big and steep!) but when you land in front of the falls the view will take your breath away! Highly recommend, especially if you sick of waiting in line for photos of waterfalls- true beauty of Bali !

name: Umah indi bali homestay
address: Banjar Gitgit, F8MH+3WC, desa, Bakbakan, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80515, Indonesia
review 1: What a great place to relax and enjoy beautiful Bali in a quaint part of Bali Situated in a village location surrounded by local culture and hospitality Mingle at a local food market Close to waterfalls And you may even experience some ceremonys The unit is cosy and relaxing You can enjoy home grown vegetables Or just read a book at your leasure on your balcony . Ubud is not far   So take time out and soak up some traditional life Ps the owner is a chef and you may be lucky to have Balinese food cooked specially for you You will always feel very welcome Enjoy your stay

name: Waterfall

name: Warung Cucu 58
address: F8GH+XR3, Bakbakan, Gianyar, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80513, Indonesia
review 1: Called in here for a light lunch on my way exploring waterfalls. I agree with the favourable reviews for this little establishment as the food was simple but fresh and tasty. I spent only 20,000Rp (less than AUD$2) including a delicious blue lychee drink. Look at the prices. Food here is great value for money and tasty as well. Word of warning though: If you need to use the bathroom, watch out for the incredibly low doorway. It was built for hobbits. I bumped my head hard, which of course is largely my own fault.
review 2: Absolutely amazing! I would give 10 stars! The best shrimps I had on Bali! Better than at much expensive ones! Also blue lychee drink is perfect!
review 3: Really good local food and super affordable prices for this quality. Highly recommend to stop here for a quick lunch on your waterfall tour.
review 4: Very nice local family restaurant with local prices. I had a fried chicken breast and it was very delicious. I recommend stopping by if you are around.
review 5: Incredible local food near Ubud. Totally recommend to eat here!

name: Umah Arya
address: Banjar Gitgit, Jl. Gn. Agung Desa, Bakbakan, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80515, Indonesia
review 1: Really wonderful to spend time in a beautiful traditional family ‘compound’. Wayan and Komang and the kids will make sure you feel special and have a happy time. Modern western bath, shower and toilet and great bed make this very comfortable. Enjoy village life nearby Ubud
review 2: close to waterfall, close to city center.

name: Abangan waterfall
address: Bakbakan, Gianyar, Gianyar Regency, Bali, Indonesia
review 1: Without doubt one of the best and untouched waterfalls in Bali, spent all morning at the waterfall and not one other tourist. Wayan was a wonderful host! You must go here!
review 2: A very panoramic scenery only 1 hr drive away from the city. Still not very crowded and the water splash feels so calming
review 3: Couldn’t recommend anymore!!! Amazing views, not crowded excellent staff extremely helpful. Expect a bit of a hike as in any others around the area
review 4: Hidden gem waterfall in Ubud. Our guide Wayan took us down to the beautiful waterfall and holy water where there were no other tourists. Would  recommend more than any others.
review 5: Really nice and peaceful place, cute waterfall, nobody there, we were alone and our guide Wayan was so amazing, 20 000 IDR per person, definitely recommend !
